$ /proc/$pid/cpuset

`/proc/$pid/cpuset` displays the path of the process's cpuset directory relative to the root of the cpuset filesystem.

{ TODO

  According to → https://stackoverflow.com/a/52988227/180275[this Stackoverflow answer], the container ID of a docker container can be determined *from within the container* with the following command:
code {
$ basename $(cat /proc/1/cpuset)
code }

